Century-old house undamaged in M 7.0 quake in SW China 
2013-04-24 06:02:16 GMT
By Yu Runze, Sina EnglishA magnitude-7.0 earthquake jolted Ya’an in southwest China’s Sichuan Province on April 20, leaving 193 people dead and over 26,411 houses damaged.Despite the devastating loss, a century-old house located in the region stood firmly and was almost undamaged except a few tiles fell on the ground.The old wooden house, where 7 families surnamed Zhang lived, was built during the Tongzhi Period (1862-1874) of late Qing Dynasty and served as the thirty Red Army headquarters.
